{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"My subject today is learning."},{"time":3000,"text":"And in that spirit, I want to spring on you all a pop quiz."},{"time":6000,"text":"Ready?"},{"time":8000,"text":"When does learning begin?"},{"time":11000,"text":"Now as you ponder that question,"},{"time":13000,"text":"maybe you're thinking about the first day of preschool"},{"time":15000,"text":"or kindergarten,"},{"time":17000,"text":"the first time that kids are in a classroom with a teacher."},{"time":20000,"text":"Or maybe you've called to mind the toddler phase"},{"time":23000,"text":"when children are learning how to walk and talk"},{"time":26000,"text":"and use a fork."},{"time":28000,"text":"Maybe you've encountered the Zero-to-Three movement,"},{"time":31000,"text":"which asserts that the most important years for learning"},{"time":34000,"text":"are the earliest ones."},{"time":36000,"text":"And so your answer to my question would be:"},{"time":39000,"text":"Learning begins at birth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41000,"text":"Well today I want to present to you"},{"time":43000,"text":"an idea that may be surprising"},{"time":46000,"text":"and may even seem implausible,"},{"time":49000,"text":"but which is supported by the latest evidence"},{"time":51000,"text":"from psychology and biology."},{"time":54000,"text":"And that is that some of the most important learning we ever do"},{"time":57000,"text":"happens before we're born,"},{"time":59000,"text":"while we're still in the womb."},{"time":62000,"text":"Now I'm a science reporter."},{"time":64000,"text":"I write books and magazine articles."},{"time":66000,"text":"And I'm also a mother."},{"time":68000,"text":"And those two roles came together for me"},{"time":71000,"text":"in a book that I wrote called \"Origins.\""},{"time":74000,"text":"\"Origins\" is a report from the front lines"},{"time":77000,"text":"of an exciting new field"},{"time":79000,"text":"called fetal origins."},{"time":81000,"text":"Fetal origins is a scientific discipline"},{"time":84000,"text":"that emerged just about two decades ago,"},{"time":87000,"text":"and it's based on the theory"},{"time":90000,"text":"that our health and well-being throughout our lives"},{"time":93000,"text":"is crucially affected"},{"time":95000,"text":"by the nine months we spend in the womb."},{"time":98000,"text":"Now this theory was of more than just intellectual interest to me."},{"time":102000,"text":"I was myself pregnant"},{"time":104000,"text":"while I was doing the research for the book."},{"time":107000,"text":"And one of the most fascinating insights"},{"time":109000,"text":"I took from this work"},{"time":111000,"text":"is that we're all learning about the world"},{"time":114000,"text":"even before we enter it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117000,"text":"When we hold our babies for the first time,"},{"time":119000,"text":"we might imagine that they're clean slates,"},{"time":122000,"text":"unmarked by life,"},{"time":124000,"text":"when in fact, they've already been shaped by us"},{"time":127000,"text":"and by the particular world we live in."},{"time":131000,"text":"Today I want to share with you some of the amazing things"},{"time":133000,"text":"that scientists are discovering"},{"time":135000,"text":"about what fetuses learn"},{"time":137000,"text":"while they're still in their mothers' bellies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"First of all,"},{"time":143000,"text":"they learn the sound of their mothers' voices."},{"time":146000,"text":"Because sounds from the outside world"},{"time":149000,"text":"have to travel through the mother's abdominal tissue"},{"time":152000,"text":"and through the amniotic fluid that surrounds the fetus,"},{"time":156000,"text":"the voices fetuses hear,"},{"time":158000,"text":"starting around the fourth month of gestation,"},{"time":161000,"text":"are muted and muffled."},{"time":163000,"text":"One researcher says"},{"time":165000,"text":"that they probably sound a lot like the the voice of Charlie Brown's teacher"},{"time":168000,"text":"in the old \"Peanuts\" cartoon."},{"time":171000,"text":"But the pregnant woman's own voice"},{"time":174000,"text":"reverberates through her body,"},{"time":176000,"text":"reaching the fetus much more readily."},{"time":179000,"text":"And because the fetus is with her all the time,"},{"time":182000,"text":"it hears her voice a lot."},{"time":185000,"text":"Once the baby's born, it recognizes her voice"},{"time":188000,"text":"and it prefers listening to her voice"},{"time":190000,"text":"over anyone else's."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192000,"text":"How can we know this?"},{"time":194000,"text":"Newborn babies can't do much,"},{"time":196000,"text":"but one thing they're really good at is sucking."},{"time":199000,"text":"Researchers take advantage of this fact"},{"time":202000,"text":"by rigging up two rubber nipples,"},{"time":205000,"text":"so that if a baby sucks on one,"},{"time":207000,"text":"it hears a recording of its mother's voice"},{"time":209000,"text":"on a pair of headphones,"},{"time":211000,"text":"and if it sucks on the other nipple,"},{"time":213000,"text":"it hears a recording of a female stranger's voice."},{"time":217000,"text":"Babies quickly show their preference"},{"time":220000,"text":"by choosing the first one."},{"time":223000,"text":"Scientists also take advantage of the fact"},{"time":226000,"text":"that babies will slow down their sucking"},{"time":228000,"text":"when something interests them"},{"time":230000,"text":"and resume their fast sucking"},{"time":232000,"text":"when they get bored."},{"time":235000,"text":"This is how researchers discovered"},{"time":237000,"text":"that, after women repeatedly read aloud"},{"time":240000,"text":"a section of Dr. Seuss' \"The Cat in the Hat\" while they were pregnant,"},{"time":244000,"text":"their newborn babies recognized that passage"},{"time":247000,"text":"when they hear it outside the womb."},{"time":250000,"text":"My favorite experiment of this kind"},{"time":253000,"text":"is the one that showed that the babies"},{"time":255000,"text":"of women who watched a certain soap opera"},{"time":257000,"text":"every day during pregnancy"},{"time":260000,"text":"recognized the theme song of that show"},{"time":263000,"text":"once they were born."},{"time":266000,"text":"So fetuses are even learning"},{"time":268000,"text":"about the particular language that's spoken"},{"time":271000,"text":"in the world that they'll be born into."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273000,"text":"A study published last year"},{"time":276000,"text":"found that from birth, from the moment of birth,"},{"time":279000,"text":"babies cry in the accent"},{"time":281000,"text":"of their mother's native language."},{"time":284000,"text":"French babies cry on a rising note"},{"time":287000,"text":"while German babies end on a falling note,"},{"time":290000,"text":"imitating the melodic contours"},{"time":292000,"text":"of those languages."},{"time":294000,"text":"Now why would this kind of fetal learning"},{"time":296000,"text":"be useful?"},{"time":298000,"text":"It may have evolved to aid the baby's survival."},{"time":301000,"text":"From the moment of birth,"},{"time":303000,"text":"the baby responds most to the voice"},{"time":305000,"text":"of the person who is most likely to care for it --"},{"time":307000,"text":"its mother."},{"time":309000,"text":"It even makes its cries"},{"time":311000,"text":"sound like the mother's language,"},{"time":313000,"text":"which may further endear the baby to the mother,"},{"time":316000,"text":"and which may give the baby a head start"},{"time":318000,"text":"in the critical task"},{"time":320000,"text":"of learning how to understand and speak"},{"time":323000,"text":"its native language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"But it's not just sounds"},{"time":327000,"text":"that fetuses are learning about in utero."},{"time":329000,"text":"It's also tastes and smells."},{"time":332000,"text":"By seven months of gestation,"},{"time":334000,"text":"the fetus' taste buds are fully developed,"},{"time":336000,"text":"and its olfactory receptors, which allow it to smell,"},{"time":339000,"text":"are functioning."},{"time":341000,"text":"The flavors of the food a pregnant woman eats"},{"time":344000,"text":"find their way into the amniotic fluid,"},{"time":346000,"text":"which is continuously swallowed"},{"time":348000,"text":"by the fetus."},{"time":350000,"text":"Babies seem to remember and prefer these tastes"},{"time":353000,"text":"once they're out in the world."},{"time":356000,"text":"In one experiment, a group of pregnant women"},{"time":359000,"text":"was asked to drink a lot of carrot juice"},{"time":361000,"text":"during their third trimester of pregnancy,"},{"time":364000,"text":"while another group of pregnant women"},{"time":366000,"text":"drank only water."},{"time":368000,"text":"Six months later, the women's infants"},{"time":371000,"text":"were offered cereal mixed with carrot juice,"},{"time":374000,"text":"and their facial expressions were observed while they ate it."},{"time":378000,"text":"The offspring of the carrot juice drinking women"},{"time":380000,"text":"ate more carrot-flavored cereal,"},{"time":382000,"text":"and from the looks of it,"},{"time":384000,"text":"they seemed to enjoy it more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386000,"text":"A sort of French version of this experiment"},{"time":389000,"text":"was carried out in Dijon, France"},{"time":391000,"text":"where researchers found"},{"time":393000,"text":"that mothers who consumed food and drink"},{"time":396000,"text":"flavored with licorice-flavored anise during pregnancy"},{"time":401000,"text":"showed a preference for anise"},{"time":403000,"text":"on their first day of life,"},{"time":405000,"text":"and again, when they were tested later,"},{"time":407000,"text":"on their fourth day of life."},{"time":409000,"text":"Babies whose mothers did not eat anise during pregnancy"},{"time":413000,"text":"showed a reaction that translated roughly as \"yuck.\""},{"time":417000,"text":"What this means"},{"time":419000,"text":"is that fetuses are effectively being taught by their mothers"},{"time":421000,"text":"about what is safe and good to eat."},{"time":424000,"text":"Fetuses are also being taught"},{"time":426000,"text":"about the particular culture that they'll be joining"},{"time":429000,"text":"through one of culture's most powerful expressions,"},{"time":432000,"text":"which is food."},{"time":434000,"text":"They're being introduced to the characteristic flavors and spices"},{"time":437000,"text":"of their culture's cuisine"},{"time":439000,"text":"even before birth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442000,"text":"Now it turns out that fetuses are learning even bigger lessons."},{"time":445000,"text":"But before I get to that,"},{"time":447000,"text":"I want to address something that you may be wondering about."},{"time":451000,"text":"The notion of fetal learning"},{"time":453000,"text":"may conjure up for you attempts to enrich the fetus --"},{"time":456000,"text":"like playing Mozart through headphones"},{"time":458000,"text":"placed on a pregnant belly."},{"time":460000,"text":"But actually, the nine-month-long process"},{"time":463000,"text":"of molding and shaping that goes on in the womb"},{"time":466000,"text":"is a lot more visceral and consequential than that."},{"time":470000,"text":"Much of what a pregnant woman encounters in her daily life --"},{"time":474000,"text":"the air she breathes,"},{"time":476000,"text":"the food and drink she consumes,"},{"time":478000,"text":"the chemicals she's exposed to,"},{"time":480000,"text":"even the emotions she feels --"},{"time":482000,"text":"are shared in some fashion with her fetus."},{"time":485000,"text":"They make up a mix of influences"},{"time":488000,"text":"as individual and idiosyncratic"},{"time":490000,"text":"as the woman herself."},{"time":492000,"text":"The fetus incorporates these offerings"},{"time":494000,"text":"into its own body,"},{"time":496000,"text":"makes them part of its flesh and blood."},{"time":499000,"text":"And often it does something more."},{"time":501000,"text":"It treats these maternal contributions"},{"time":504000,"text":"as information,"},{"time":506000,"text":"as what I like to call biological postcards"},{"time":508000,"text":"from the world outside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511000,"text":"So what a fetus is learning about in utero"},{"time":514000,"text":"is not Mozart's \"Magic Flute\""},{"time":516000,"text":"but answers to questions much more critical to its survival."},{"time":520000,"text":"Will it be born into a world of abundance"},{"time":522000,"text":"or scarcity?"},{"time":524000,"text":"Will it be safe and protected,"},{"time":527000,"text":"or will it face constant dangers and threats?"},{"time":530000,"text":"Will it live a long, fruitful life"},{"time":532000,"text":"or a short, harried one?"},{"time":535000,"text":"The pregnant woman's diet and stress level in particular"},{"time":538000,"text":"provide important clues to prevailing conditions"},{"time":541000,"text":"like a finger lifted to the wind."},{"time":544000,"text":"The resulting tuning and tweaking"},{"time":546000,"text":"of a fetus' brain and other organs"},{"time":549000,"text":"are part of what give us humans"},{"time":551000,"text":"our enormous flexibility,"},{"time":553000,"text":"our ability to thrive"},{"time":555000,"text":"in a huge variety of environments,"},{"time":557000,"text":"from the country to the city,"},{"time":559000,"text":"from the tundra to the desert."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562000,"text":"To conclude, I want to tell you two stories"},{"time":564000,"text":"about how mothers teach their children about the world"},{"time":567000,"text":"even before they're born."},{"time":571000,"text":"In the autumn of 1944,"},{"time":573000,"text":"the darkest days of World War II,"},{"time":576000,"text":"German troops blockaded Western Holland,"},{"time":579000,"text":"turning away all shipments of food."},{"time":582000,"text":"The opening of the Nazi's siege"},{"time":584000,"text":"was followed by one of the harshest winters in decades --"},{"time":587000,"text":"so cold the water in the canals froze solid."},{"time":591000,"text":"Soon food became scarce,"},{"time":593000,"text":"with many Dutch surviving on just 500 calories a day --"},{"time":597000,"text":"a quarter of what they consumed before the war."},{"time":600000,"text":"As weeks of deprivation stretched into months,"},{"time":603000,"text":"some resorted to eating tulip bulbs."},{"time":606000,"text":"By the beginning of May,"},{"time":608000,"text":"the nation's carefully rationed food reserve"},{"time":610000,"text":"was completely exhausted."},{"time":612000,"text":"The specter of mass starvation loomed."},{"time":615000,"text":"And then on May 5th, 1945,"},{"time":618000,"text":"the siege came to a sudden end"},{"time":620000,"text":"when Holland was liberated"},{"time":622000,"text":"by the Allies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624000,"text":"The \"Hunger Winter,\" as it came to be known,"},{"time":627000,"text":"killed some 10,000 people"},{"time":629000,"text":"and weakened thousands more."},{"time":631000,"text":"But there was another population that was affected --"},{"time":634000,"text":"the 40,000 fetuses"},{"time":636000,"text":"in utero during the siege."},{"time":639000,"text":"Some of the effects of malnutrition during pregnancy"},{"time":641000,"text":"were immediately apparent"},{"time":643000,"text":"in higher rates of stillbirths,"},{"time":645000,"text":"birth defects, low birth weights"},{"time":647000,"text":"and infant mortality."},{"time":649000,"text":"But others wouldn't be discovered for many years."},{"time":652000,"text":"Decades after the \"Hunger Winter,\""},{"time":654000,"text":"researchers documented"},{"time":656000,"text":"that people whose mothers were pregnant during the siege"},{"time":660000,"text":"have more obesity, more diabetes"},{"time":662000,"text":"and more heart disease in later life"},{"time":665000,"text":"than individuals who were gestated under normal conditions."},{"time":668000,"text":"These individuals' prenatal experience of starvation"},{"time":672000,"text":"seems to have changed their bodies"},{"time":674000,"text":"in myriad ways."},{"time":676000,"text":"They have higher blood pressure,"},{"time":678000,"text":"poorer cholesterol profiles"},{"time":680000,"text":"and reduced glucose tolerance --"},{"time":682000,"text":"a precursor of diabetes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685000,"text":"Why would undernutrition in the womb"},{"time":687000,"text":"result in disease later?"},{"time":689000,"text":"One explanation"},{"time":691000,"text":"is that fetuses are making the best of a bad situation."},{"time":694000,"text":"When food is scarce,"},{"time":696000,"text":"they divert nutrients towards the really critical organ, the brain,"},{"time":699000,"text":"and away from other organs"},{"time":701000,"text":"like the heart and liver."},{"time":703000,"text":"This keeps the fetus alive in the short-term,"},{"time":706000,"text":"but the bill comes due later on in life"},{"time":709000,"text":"when those other organs, deprived early on,"},{"time":711000,"text":"become more susceptible to disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714000,"text":"But that may not be all that's going on."},{"time":717000,"text":"It seems that fetuses are taking cues"},{"time":719000,"text":"from the intrauterine environment"},{"time":722000,"text":"and tailoring their physiology accordingly."},{"time":724000,"text":"They're preparing themselves"},{"time":726000,"text":"for the kind of world they will encounter"},{"time":728000,"text":"on the other side of the womb."},{"time":730000,"text":"The fetus adjusts its metabolism"},{"time":732000,"text":"and other physiological processes"},{"time":735000,"text":"in anticipation of the environment that awaits it."},{"time":738000,"text":"And the basis of the fetus' prediction"},{"time":741000,"text":"is what its mother eats."},{"time":743000,"text":"The meals a pregnant woman consumes"},{"time":745000,"text":"constitute a kind of story,"},{"time":747000,"text":"a fairy tale of abundance"},{"time":749000,"text":"or a grim chronicle of deprivation."},{"time":752000,"text":"This story imparts information"},{"time":755000,"text":"that the fetus uses"},{"time":757000,"text":"to organize its body and its systems --"},{"time":759000,"text":"an adaptation to prevailing circumstances"},{"time":762000,"text":"that facilitates its future survival."},{"time":765000,"text":"Faced with severely limited resources,"},{"time":768000,"text":"a smaller-sized child with reduced energy requirements"},{"time":771000,"text":"will, in fact, have a better chance"},{"time":773000,"text":"of living to adulthood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775000,"text":"The real trouble comes"},{"time":777000,"text":"when pregnant women are, in a sense, unreliable narrators,"},{"time":780000,"text":"when fetuses are led"},{"time":782000,"text":"to expect a world of scarcity"},{"time":784000,"text":"and are born instead into a world of plenty."},{"time":787000,"text":"This is what happened to the children of the Dutch \"Hunger Winter.\""},{"time":790000,"text":"And their higher rates of obesity,"},{"time":792000,"text":"diabetes and heart disease"},{"time":794000,"text":"are the result."},{"time":796000,"text":"Bodies that were built to hang onto every calorie"},{"time":799000,"text":"found themselves swimming in the superfluous calories"},{"time":801000,"text":"of the post-war Western diet."},{"time":804000,"text":"The world they had learned about while in utero"},{"time":807000,"text":"was not the same"},{"time":809000,"text":"as the world into which they were born."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812000,"text":"Here's another story."},{"time":814000,"text":"At 8:46 a.m. on September 11th, 2001,"},{"time":818000,"text":"there were tens of thousands of people"},{"time":820000,"text":"in the vicinity of the World Trade Center"},{"time":822000,"text":"in New York --"},{"time":824000,"text":"commuters spilling off trains,"},{"time":826000,"text":"waitresses setting tables for the morning rush,"},{"time":829000,"text":"brokers already working the phones on Wall Street."},{"time":833000,"text":"1,700 of these people were pregnant women."},{"time":836000,"text":"When the planes struck and the towers collapsed,"},{"time":839000,"text":"many of these women experienced the same horrors"},{"time":842000,"text":"inflicted on other survivors of the disaster --"},{"time":845000,"text":"the overwhelming chaos and confusion,"},{"time":847000,"text":"the rolling clouds"},{"time":849000,"text":"of potentially toxic dust and debris,"},{"time":853000,"text":"the heart-pounding fear for their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":855000,"text":"About a year after 9/11,"},{"time":857000,"text":"researchers examined a group of women"},{"time":860000,"text":"who were pregnant"},{"time":862000,"text":"when they were exposed to the World Trade Center attack."},{"time":864000,"text":"In the babies of those women"},{"time":866000,"text":"who developed post-traumatic stress syndrome, or PTSD,"},{"time":869000,"text":"following their ordeal,"},{"time":871000,"text":"researchers discovered a biological marker"},{"time":874000,"text":"of susceptibility to PTSD --"},{"time":876000,"text":"an effect that was most pronounced"},{"time":879000,"text":"in infants whose mothers experienced the catastrophe"},{"time":882000,"text":"in their third trimester."},{"time":884000,"text":"In other words,"},{"time":886000,"text":"the mothers with post-traumatic stress syndrome"},{"time":889000,"text":"had passed on a vulnerability to the condition"},{"time":892000,"text":"to their children while they were still in utero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895000,"text":"Now consider this:"},{"time":897000,"text":"post-traumatic stress syndrome"},{"time":899000,"text":"appears to be a reaction to stress gone very wrong,"},{"time":902000,"text":"causing its victims tremendous unnecessary suffering."},{"time":906000,"text":"But there's another way of thinking about PTSD."},{"time":909000,"text":"What looks like pathology to us"},{"time":912000,"text":"may actually be a useful adaptation"},{"time":914000,"text":"in some circumstances."},{"time":916000,"text":"In a particularly dangerous environment,"},{"time":919000,"text":"the characteristic manifestations of PTSD --"},{"time":922000,"text":"a hyper-awareness of one's surroundings,"},{"time":925000,"text":"a quick-trigger response to danger --"},{"time":928000,"text":"could save someone's life."},{"time":931000,"text":"The notion that the prenatal transmission of PTSD risk is adaptive"},{"time":935000,"text":"is still speculative,"},{"time":937000,"text":"but I find it rather poignant."},{"time":940000,"text":"It would mean that, even before birth,"},{"time":942000,"text":"mothers are warning their children"},{"time":944000,"text":"that it's a wild world out there,"},{"time":946000,"text":"telling them, \"Be careful.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":949000,"text":"Let me be clear."},{"time":951000,"text":"Fetal origins research is not about blaming women"},{"time":954000,"text":"for what happens during pregnancy."},{"time":956000,"text":"It's about discovering how best to promote"},{"time":959000,"text":"the health and well-being of the next generation."},{"time":962000,"text":"That important effort must include a focus"},{"time":964000,"text":"on what fetuses learn"},{"time":966000,"text":"during the nine months they spend in the womb."},{"time":969000,"text":"Learning is one of life's most essential activities,"},{"time":972000,"text":"and it begins much earlier"},{"time":974000,"text":"than we ever imagined."}]},{"cues":[{"time":976000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":978000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}